{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "Facing the prospect of impossibly long waiting lists for organs, some patients have turned to an underground trade that pairs them with people willing to sell an organ.", "abstract": "New York Times analysis of major organ trafficking cases since 2000 suggests that Israeli organ brokers have played disproportionate role in global organ trade; documents show Israeli brokers Avigad Sandler, Boris Volfman and Yaacov Dayan are among the central operators in Israel's underground kidney market, and have pocketed enormous sums for arranging overseas transplants for patients who are paired with foreign donors, many from impoverished countries.", "section_name": "World", "print_page": "1", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Kevin", "role": "reported", "lastname": "SACK", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By KEVIN SACK", "contributor": "Irit Pazner Garshowitz contributed reporting from Jerusalem, and M\u00f3nica Quesada Cordero from San Jos\u00e9, Costa Rica."}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/08/17/world/middleeast/transplant-brokers-in-israel-lure-desperate-kidney-patients-to-costa-rica.html", "lead_paragraph": "Facing the prospect of impossibly long waiting lists for organs, some patients have turned to an underground trade that pairs them with people willing to sell an organ.", "headline": {"main": "Transplant Brokers in Israel Lure Desperate Kidney Patients to Costa Rica", "print_headline": "Kidneys for Sale"}, "_id": "53f045d838f0d879cfc5858b", "word_count": "5467", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2014/08/17/world/17organs-ophira/17organs-ophira-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2014/08/17/world/17organs-ophira/17organs-ophira-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 400, "url": "images/2014/08/17/world/17organs-ophira/17organs-ophira-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images